This paper is most likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) category as it deals with sponsored search and advertisement slots. The paper also discusses auction mechanisms, which are commonly used in sponsored search and are a topic of interest in Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel structure for ad options, which could be considered a topic in Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses option pricing methods, which could be considered a topic in Computational Economics (cs.CE).
